description.value: Ostracon from the rim of a pottery vessel in the shape of a plate, wheel made, Nile clay, red band around the rim at inside and outside. Eroded at the inside. The outside shows two lines of hieratic script in black ink, the second one is framed by a black line forming a shape that is flat at the top and roughly semi circular at the base (like a bowl).

description.value: Small fragment of an ostracon from a pottery, showing two lines of hieratic on the outside of the vessel written in black ink.  The sherd belonged to a closed shaped vessel, probably an amphora, it shows a greenish cream slip on the outside that was burnished partly. The inside of the vessel is coloured by a black substance which might be remains of the original content?

description.value: Fragment of an ostracon from a pottery vessel that shows different signs on the outside of the vessel, written or rather drawn in black ink as it seems more to be motifs than textual signs. Three lines are distinguishable.  The sherd is part of the rim of a plate with a small ledge at the inside, diameter about 25cm, remains of a black substance at the inside. Probably Nile clay, some chaff inclusions and mica, wheel made.

description.value: Fragment of an ostracon from a pottery vessel, parts of three lines of hieratic written in black ink are preserved, the rest is broken off. Maybe a list, as the same sign seems to be repeated in a smaller scale in each line.  The vessel is made of Nile clay, closed shape, cream slip on outside, wheel made, most likely an amphora. The object was glued. Some white accretions on surface.

description.value: Ostracon made of a pottery sherd from the rim of an egyptian plate or bowl of about 20cm in diameter, wheel made, Nile clay with some chaff, mica and white lime bits. The vessel bears a red band around the rim at inside and outside. The outside shows three lines of hieratic script in black ink, parallel to the rim, the inside shows another line of hieratic but much fainter. Inside also white accretions.
